# Code Quality Standards

## TypeScript
- Strict mode is on — never use `any`. Prefer explicit types or inferred generics.
- Use `@/*` path aliases instead of relative imports deeper than one level.
- Prefer `const` over `let`; never use `var`.

## React / Next.js
- Functional components only. Use hooks for state and side effects.
- Colocate component-specific types in the same file.
- Keep components under ~150 lines; extract logic into custom hooks or utils.
- Use server components by default; add `"use client"` only when the component needs browser APIs, state, or event handlers.

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes. Avoid inline `style` props and separate CSS files.
- Keep class lists readable — extract to variables or `cn()` helper when they exceed ~5 utilities.

## Error Handling
- Never swallow errors. Always log or re-throw with context.
- API routes must return proper HTTP status codes and structured JSON errors.

## File Organization
- Pages in `src/app/`, components in `src/components/`, utilities in `src/lib/`.
- One exported component per file. Name the file to match the export.

## Before Finishing
- Run `npm run lint` and fix all errors before committing.
- Run `npm run build` to catch type errors before pushing.
